============================================================

Written the improvement plan to `tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md`.

**Summary of the 9 proposed changes:**

1. **Case normalization** (~20 fixes) — Convert ALL_CAPS output to Title Case as the final step. Biggest single win.
2. **Polish prepositions in `commonShort2`** (2 fixes) — Add `ze`, `bo`, `na`, `po`, `od`, `za`, `co` so they're not flagged as garbled.
3. **Protect multi-line joins from component dedup** (~4 fixes) — When `Lamb Stew` (join) and `Lamb` + `Stew` (singles) all survive, remove the singles.
4. **Context-aware section label join blocking** (1 fix) — Allow joins starting with section labels when result has ≥3 words (`Zupy Zimowe Warzywne`).
5. **Content-based garbage prologue detection** (~12 fixes) — Filter lines starting with imperative cooking verbs (≥4 words) as instructions, not title candidates.
6. **Add `SEZON:` to metadata patterns** (~2 fixes) — Trivial filter gap.
7. **Strip parenthetical English glosses** (~5 fixes) — Remove `(Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)` from `PIEROGI RUSKIE`.
8. **Position-aware compound dedup** (1 fix) — Protect position-0 compound titles from distant sub-headers.
9. **Page number prefix stripping** (1 fix) — Extract `Berry Jam` from `34  Berry Jam`.

Expected: **48–52 of 54 failures fixed**, bringing pass rate to ~96–98%. Two failures (OCR character substitution, missing OCR word) are accepted as unfixable at this layer.
