plemented. They fixed the \"Faszerowana papryka\" case on real data.\n\nHowever, when tested against the broader synthetic corpus (203 files), the changes introduced 54 new failures. These are categorized into 8 patterns:\n\n1. **ALL_CAPS vs. Title Case mismatch (~20 failures)** — Algorithm returns OCR casing exactly as found; tests expect canonical mixed-case. This is a test-expectation issue, not an algorithm bug.\n2. **Polish short preposition `ze` flagged as garbled** — Not in `commonShort2` set\n3. **Two-word titles split across lines destroyed by dedup** — Dedup rule removes the 2-line join when both component words pass independently\n4. **Three-line title where first word is in SECTION_LABELS** — The join-block logic prevents multi-line reconstruction\n5. **Long OCR garbage prologue (~12 failures)** — Burst detection only handles short lines (<20 chars); these are 30-55 chars\n6. **Season/context headers (SEZON: WIOSNA) scoring higher than titles** — No metadata pattern for `SEZON:`\n7. **Parenthetical English subtitles over-merged** — `(` continuation pre-merge was too aggressive\n8. **Compound titles destroyed by substring dedup** — `HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION` removed because it contains `DILL SAUCE VARIATION`\n\n#### **Iteration 16 → 17**\n**Proposed changes** (never implemented due to worse test results in 18):\n- Extended bilingual suppression to catch translations embedded as suffixes/middle of multi-line joins\n- Reassigned structural bonus when heading identified as translation\n- Diacritic-insensitive section label matching\n\n**Failure being fixed**: `Smażona zielona fasolka` returning empty string\n\n#### **Iteration 15 → 16**\n**Context**: Previous iteration had 3 failures; this focused on understanding \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" better\n\n**Key insight**: The root problem was bilingual join contamination — the algorithm suppressed standalone translation candidates but multi-line joins embedding translations remained, with their composite embeddings (Polish + English) scoring higher than the Polish-only title.\n\n#### **Iteration 14 → 15**\n**Changes attempted**:\n1. Filter forward-slash-separated breadcrumbs (`/ Jesien / Zupy`) — added to METADATA_PATTERNS or as new check\n2. Improved garbled-text detection for 4-letter mixed-case words like `UuIw`\n3. Added `DLA & OSOB` variant handling (OCR `4` → `&`)\n\n**Failures being fixed**:\n- `KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA` returning `UuIw` (breadcrumb bilingual false positive)\n- `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` returning `BALLS` (metadata fragment pollution)\n- `Smażona zielona fasolka` returning `DLA & OSOB` (OCR-corrupted metadata winning via ALL_CAPS bonus)\n\n#### **Iteration 13 → 14**\n**Status**: First \"clean-ish\" run with most patterns working\n\n**Known failures at start**:\n- 4-line titles can't be assembled (only up to 3-line joins)\n- `WITH NIGELLA` substring dedup destroying 3-line join\n- ALL_CAPS structural bonus overriding mixed-case titles\n\n#### **Iterations 1-13 (Baseline)**\nBaseline loop creating candidates, hard filters, embedding scoring, threshold cutoff, dedup.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Decisions**\n\nFrom `architecture.md`, the current pipeline is:\n1. Split into lines + burst-end detection (discard short garbled start)\n2. Pre-merge continuation lines (`/&+:(`)\n3. Generate candidates (single, 2-line, 3-line joins)\n4. Hard filters (9 independent checks)\n5. Cap at 25 candidates for embedding API\n6. Embedding scoring (title similarity − max(header, noise))\n7. Structural heading selection (best ALL_CAPS)\n8. OCR truncation penalty\n9. Bonuses (position ×1.12, ALL_CAPS +0.08, structural +0.10)\n10. Bilingual detection (suppress translations)\n11. Threshold filter\n12. Post-threshold cleanup (prefix removal, join protection, sub-section removal)\n13. Dedup (shorter substring wins)\n14. Multi-title guard (2+ ALL_CAPS → check ingredients; 1 ALL_CAPS → highest score)\n15. Sort/cap/join final results\n\n---\n\n### **Patterns of Failure & Reverted Approaches**\n\n**Reverted/Blocked Changes**:\n- Iter 17's improvements were never fully applied to real code due to iter 18 regression testing against synthetic corpus\n- Architectural changes to dedup and join logic explicitly marked \"DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC\" after multiple failed attempts in iterations 1-7\n\n**Recurring Failure Modes**:\n1. **ALL_CAPS bias system misfiring** — Designed to prefer recipe titles but elevates section labels (iter 17)\n2. **Bilingual detection brittleness** — Works for some language pairs but fails for cross-lingual (Polish + Korean) embeddings (iter 14-16)\n3. **Burst detection too narrow** — Only < 20 chars; fails on 30+ char repeated garbage (iter 18)\n4. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" oversimplification** — Correct for 90% of cases but breaks on compound titles or when parts independently pass filters (iter 15, 18)\n5. **Section label false positives** — `Zupy` blocks 3-line reconstruction when it's actually the start of a title, not a category (iter 18)\n6. **Metadata pattern gaps** — Missing `SEZON:`, `DLA & OSOB` (OCR with `&`), forward-slash breadcrumbs (iter 15, 18)\n7. **Non-ASCII short-word handling** — Polish `ze` not in `commonShort2`; non-ASCII stripping breaks 2-letter prepositions (iter 18)\n\n---\n\n### **What Actually Works Well**\n\n- Core embedding-based scoring (title similarity − header/noise)\n- Position bonus (multiplicative, not additive)\n- Hard filters (9 independent checks catch most junk)\n- Continuation pre-merge for `/&+:(` lines\n- Structural heading selection (best ALL_CAPS candidate)\n- Bilingual detection *when* embeddings align (iter 17's fixes help here)\n- Dedup for truly duplicate/redundant candidates (when no legitimate compounds exist)\n\n---\n\n### **The Real Issue at Iteration 18**\n\nThe synthetic test corpus (203 files) appears to be generated and contains patterns not representative of real recipe photos (11 real files at 100% accuracy). The automated loop is 