{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WyQM81PKvfTZM2cs7HyTU7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the problem. Let me analyze each failure pattern and propose changes.\n\nKey insights:\n1. ~20 failures are just ALL_CAPS → Title Case normalization (Pattern 1) - needs a case normalization step\n2. Pattern 2: `ze` missing from commonShort2 - trivial fix\n3. Pattern 3: Dedup destroys compound joins - need to protect multi-line joins from their components\n4. Pattern 4: Section labels blocking joins - need context-aware join logic\n5. Pattern 5: Long garbage prologues - need better burst/garbage detection\n\n\n6. Pattern 6: SEZON metadata not being recognized - add to METADATA_PATTERNS\n7. Pattern 7: Parenthetical over-merge - strip parentheticals before processing\n8. Pattern 8: Compound title destroyed by substring dedup - protect line-1 compounds from dedup\n9. Pattern 9: Page number prefix interfering - need smarter startsWithNumber detection\n10. Pattern 10: OCR character substitution - digit-to-letter corrections needed\n11. Pattern 11: Missing word in OCR - unfixable without external knowledge\n\nFor the approach, I'll start with a toTitleCase() normalization as a final step to handle the ALL_CAPS cases, then work through the other patterns systematically.\n\nFor Pattern 2, I just need to expand the commonShort2 list with \"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"do\" - straightforward addition.\n\nPattern 3 is trickier: the dedup logic removes \"Lamb Stew\" because it contains \"Lamb\", so I need to protect multi-line joins where all components are present as singles, preferring the joined result over individual parts.\n\nPattern 4 requires allowing joins even when a section label starts the sequence, as long as the combined result reads like a title rather than a section header like \"Zupy Składniki\".\n\nFor Pattern 5, I'm rethinking burst detection entirely - instead of just looking for short garbled lines, I should detect repeated or templated content by counting instruction-like lines before finding title candidates.\n\nPattern 6 is trivial: add the SEZON regex to metadata patterns.\n\nPattern 7 needs to handle parenthetical suffixes better, either by stripping them from candidates or avoiding merges when the parenthetical content is mixed-case English.\n\nPattern 8 protects position-0 candidates from being removed by substrings found later, or prioritizes longer candidates at the start over shorter ones elsewhere.\n\nFor Pattern 9, I'm checking how to handle page numbers...\n\nWhen a line starts with digits followed by spaces and then title-like text, I should strip that page number prefix. Pattern 10 involves common OCR substitutions like 1→l or 0→o, which I could add as a cleanup step. Now I'm ready to write out the improvement plan.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":604,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2819,"cache_read_input_tokens":45024,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2819},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc97eaa2-7481-42f4-b7bf-89f7efc643c7","uuid":"4be0f3d1-67b7-4ad1-bf14-b0ef1fdd8ea5"}
